Sure! Here's a more informal and warm Christmas card message for your colleague:


---

Dear [Colleague's Name],

Wishing you a Merry Christmas and a fantastic New Year! I just wanted to take a moment to say a huge thank you for all the hard work, dedication, and incredible leadership you've shown this year. Your technical skills, clear planning, and thoughtful guidance have made such a positive impact on the team, and I really appreciate everything you do.

It's been a pleasure working alongside you, and I'm grateful for all the support you've given. Enjoy your well-deserved break and here's to more amazing achievements in the year ahead!

Warm wishes,
[Your Name]


---

This tone is friendly and appreciative without being too formal!

